Description: Virgin Mary seated amid trees and vegetation, her hair in plaits and tied with a long cloth, cradles the baby Jesus on her lap; above, a winged cherub; to the right, a rabbit. Mezzotint
Curator's comments: Chaloner Smith lists a number of mezzotints under A(lexander) Browne, which were published by him and have no engraver name, whilst noting that it is unlikely Browne himself engraved them.
Bibliographic references: Chaloner Smith 1883 / British Mezzotinto portraits from the introduction of the art to the early part of the present century (undescribed) (under Browne)
Blackett-Ord & Turner 2008 / Early Mezzotints: Prints Published by Richard Tompson and Alexander Browne (B.66)
Acquisition notes: From Richard Ford's collection of prints after Correggio (1837,0408.14 to 669), purchased from him through Colnaghi's, for £250.
